PREFACE.

THE date of the foundation of Arbroath is of some interest in Church and public history. Thomas a Becket, the high church Archbishop‚ was slain at the altar of his own church of Canter- bury, on the 29th of December 1170. Two years after- wardS, in 1173, he was canonized3 and within five years of his canonization‚ and not more than seven from the period of his death, in the year 1178st William King of Scotland had founded, endowed, and dedicated to Saint Thomas the Martyr, the Abbey of Arbroath.
